quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  68,43,"They shall stand with eyes downcast, utterly humbled; because during their safe and sound earthly life they were called upon to prostrate themselves but they refused to do so"
  68,44,"O Prophet, leave to Me those who reject this revelation. We shall lead them step by step to their ruin, in ways that they cannot perceive"
  68,45,I shall even put up with them for a while; for My plan is fool proof
  68,46,"Or have you, O Prophet, demanded a compensation from them, that they are overburdened with debt"
  68,47,Or do they have the knowledge of the unseen and they are writing it down
  68,48,"So wait with patience for the Judgment of your Lord and be not like the man of the fish (reference is to the Prophet Jonah who was swallowed by a whale), who cried when he was in distress"
  68,49,"Had his Lord not bestowed on him His grace, he would certainly have been cast off on the naked shore, while he was condemned"
  68,50,But his Lord choose him and included him among the righteous
  68,51,"The unbelievers would almost trip you up with their eyes when they hear Our revelations (The Qur’an), and say: \"He (Muhammad) is surely crazy"
  68,52,This (The Qur’an) is nothing but a Reminder to all the people of the world
  69,1,The Haqqah
  69,2,What is the Haqqah
  69,3,And what will make you understand what the Haqqah is
  69,4,The Thamud and the ‘Ad people denied the striking calamity
  69,5,"As for Thamud, they were destroyed by the Thunderbolt"
  69,6,As for 'Ad they were destroyed by a furious windstorm
  69,7,"which He let loose on them for seven nights and eight successive days. Had you been there, you would have seen them lying prostrate as though they were hollow trunks of the palm-trees"
  69,8,"Now, do you see any of them alive"